This paper deals with active learning, which is a subfield of machine learning (cs.LG) that focuses on selecting the most informative examples to label in order to improve the performance of a classifier. The paper also involves using logged data, which is a common topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and natural language processing (cs.CL). Additionally, the paper may be relevant to the subfield of cybersecurity (cs.CR) due to the potential applications of active learning in detecting and preventing malicious activity. Finally, the paper may also be relevant to the subfield of cyber-physical systems (cs.CY) due to the potential applications of active learning in optimizing the performance of physical systems.
